From f671d5d19db5c3d6c999b885485c019ecbf06ec7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: vllm-shim <vllm-shim@local>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] feat(triton): enable AFP4WFP4 GEMM on gfx942 via BF16
 decomposition

Two changes that together let Quark MXFP4 checkpoints run on MI300X:

1. arch_info.is_fp4_avail() includes gfx942. Every aiter Triton FP4
   entrypoint asserts is_fp4_avail() unconditionally; upstream gates
   on native-FP4 archs only (gfx950, gfx1250) and the assert fires
   at the first MXFP4 forward on gfx942. gfx942 has no native FP4
   MFMA, but tl.dot_scaled decomposes the FP4 inputs to BF16 at the
   MFMA boundary and runs on the standard BF16 m16n16k16 path. Every
   call site is a pure assert (no result-based dispatch), so widening
   here covers ~10 entrypoints in one place instead of patching each
   one. is_gluon_avail() and is_mx_scale_preshuffling_avail() are
   left gfx95+ on purpose: those features have no BF16 fallback.

2. Ship configs/gemm/gfx942-GEMM-AFP4WFP4.json. Once the assert is
   relaxed, gemm_afp4wfp4 reads its tuned config via get_gemm_config,
   which requires the default {arch}-{config_name}.json to exist and
   raises AssertionError otherwise. Upstream ships only gfx1250 for
   GEMM-AFP4WFP4 and its BLOCK_SIZE_K=256 + num_stages=3 would need
   ~96KB LDS for the B tile alone -- doesn't fit gfx942's 64KB. The
   hand-rolled gfx942 default uses BLOCK_SIZE_K=128 + num_stages=2 to
   stay within LDS, covers the standard M_LEQ bucket ladder plus an
   'any' fallback, and pins matrix_instr_nonkdim=16 so the BF16 MFMA
   decomposition lands on m16n16k16. Values aren't auto-tuned;
   performance is sub-optimal until someone runs a real sweep.

Decomposed FP4 is correct but slower than native FP4 hardware. Not
upstreamed; the shim carries this locally.
